                                            <p class="bn-arbitrator-role">IPR &amp; Technology Arbitrator</p>
                                            <p class="bn-arbitrator-location"><i class="fa fa-map-marker" aria-hidden="true"/> Delhi</p>
                                            <p class="bn-arbitrator-bio">Specializes in arbitration involving intellectual property, technology, and innovation-driven disputes. He assists businesses, creators, and startups in resolving trademark, copyright, patent, and licensing conflicts through confidential and efficient arbitral proceedings.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </article>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-sm-6 col-lg-4">
                                    <article class="bn-arbitrator-card">
                                        <div class="bn-arbitrator-photo-wrap">
                                            <img src="/bharatnyay_website/static/src/img/arbitrators/parambir-singh-ghotra.jpg"
                                                 alt="Parambir Singh Ghotra — Banking &amp; Finance Arbitrator"
                                                 class="bn-arbitrator-photo"
                                                 loading="lazy"/>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="bn-arbitrator-body">
                                            <h3 class="bn-arbitrator-name">Parambir Singh Ghotra</h3>
                                            <p class="bn-arbitrator-role">Banking &amp; Finance Arbitrator</p>
                                            <p class="bn-arbitrator-location"><i class="fa fa-map-marker" aria-hidden="true"/> Chandigarh</p>
                                            <p class="bn-arbitrator-bio">Focuses on arbitration involving banking, infrastructure, finance, and SARFAESI-related disputes. Known for balancing legal precision with commercial practicality.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </article>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-sm-6 col-lg-4">
                                    <article class="bn-arbitrator-card">
                                        <div class="bn-arbitrator-photo-wrap">
                                            <img src="/bharatnyay_website/static/src/img/arbitrators/paramvir-singh-randhawa.jpg"
                                                 alt="Paramvir Singh Randhawa — Real Estate Arbitrator"
                                                 class="bn-arbitrator-photo"
                                                 loading="lazy"/>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="bn-arbitrator-body">
                                            <h3 class="bn-arbitrator-name">Paramvir Singh Randhawa</h3>
                                            <p class="bn-arbitrator-role">Real Estate Arbitrator</p>
                                            <p class="bn-arbitrator-location"><i class="fa fa-map-marker" aria-hidden="true"/> Punjab</p>
                                            <p class="bn-arbitrator-bio">Experienced in arbitrating disputes relating to real estate, construction, and RERA matters. Promotes efficient dispute resolution while preserving long-term commercial relationships.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </article>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <section class="bn-about-body bn-about-body--alt" id="proceedings">
                        <div class="container">
                            <div class="row gy-5">
                                <div class="col-lg-6" id="model-clause">
                                    <div class="bn-about-panel">
                                        <span class="bn-prose-kicker">Governance</span>
                                        <h2>Institutional coherence</h2>
                                        <p class="bn-prose-lead">Model clauses unify seat, arbitrator panel rules, escalation matrices, confidentiality carve-outs,
                                            and tribunal secretariat expectations — BharatNyay pre-populates placeholders so legal teams adapt quickly.</p>
                                        <div class="bn-next-step-card">
                                            <span class="bn-next-step-label">Next step</span>
                                            <p>Work through wording with your conflict counsel — we supply clause libraries analogous to disclosures many ODR institutions publish openly.</p>
                                            <a href="/odr/model-clause" class="btn bn-cta-orange btn-sm rounded-pill">Open clause playbook</a>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-lg-6" id="standards">
                                    <div class="bn-about-panel">
                                        <span class="bn-prose-kicker">Standards</span>
                                        <h2>Standards worth rehearsing here</h2>
                                        <p class="bn-prose-lead">Impartiality, independence, disclosures, caucus secrecy, proportional discovery, and data minimisation —
                                            these remain non-negotiable across every BharatNyay programme (ICODR &amp; NCTDR-aligned practice notes).</p>
                                        <div class="bn-standard-pills">
                                            <span class="bn-standard-pill bn-standard-pill--blue">Impartial neutrality</span>
                                            <span class="bn-standard-pill bn-standard-pill--navy">RBI fair practice overlays</span>
                                            <span class="bn-standard-pill bn-standard-pill--outline">Arbitration Act 1996 fit</span>
                                        </div>
                                        <a href="/features" class="bn-link-accent d-inline-block mt-4">Explore platform safeguards →</a>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <section class="bn-about-tech">
                        <div class="container">
                            <div class="row align-items-stretch gy-4">
                                <div class="col-lg-6">
                                    <div class="bn-about-panel bn-about-panel--dark">
                                        <span class="bn-prose-kicker">Programmes</span>
                                        <h2><span>BharatNyay ·</span> Built for governed dispute programmes</h2>
                                        <p class="bn-prose-lead">Whether you run lending recovery, enterprise contract desks, or court-referred ADR streams,
                                            BharatNyay gives every stakeholder a clear, auditable path from notice to outcome.</p>
                                        <ul class="bn-tech-list">
                                            <li>Structured proceedings aligned with the Arbitration Act 1996 and fair-practice expectations.</li>
                                            <li>Role-based workspaces for parties, neutrals, and programme administrators.</li>
                                            <li>Transparent timelines, disclosures, and hearing records for supervisory review.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-lg-6">
                                    <aside class="bn-architecture-card">
                                        <h4>Start a conversation</h4>
                                        <p>Tell us about your dispute programme — we’ll walk through proceedings design, neutrality policy, empanelment, and rollout with your legal and operations teams.</p>
                                        <a href="/contactus" class="btn bn-cta-orange">Speak with our team</a>
                                    </aside>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                </div>
                <div class="bn-landing-root">
                    <t t-call="bharatnyay_website.bn_public_footer"/>
                </div>
            </div>
        </t>
    </template>
</odoo>
